embed.alt: A precise side-profile silhouette of a California grizzly bear in mid-stride, its iconic form directly inspired by the state flag. The bear’s figure serves as a canvas for a double-exposed landscape of arid California hills and golden chaparral beneath a wide evening horizon. Radiant amber and ochre tones bathe the internal scene, blending fur texture seamlessly into terrain transitions, with shoulder ridges flowing into hill crests and a backlit flare tracing the spine. Soft shadows define the bear’s contours against a clean monochrome background, framed in a flat, centered composition with mild grain, balanced exposure, and low-key saturation, as if shot with a 50mm lens.

A winding stone bridge of weathered bricks stretches across a vast chasm shrouded in mist, leading toward an immense, circular arch made of jagged, moss-covered ruins. Set within the arch is a colossal, unblinking eye with a vertical slit pupil, its iris glowing in eerie shades of teal and crimson, radiating a molten sunset light that spills into the surrounding clouds. The arch itself is fused with twisted, leafless trees, one of which has a smaller reptilian eye peering out from the bark. Patches of pink-blossomed foliage cling to the structure, their color stark against the desaturated stone and turquoise haze. Tiny figures make their way along the fractured bridge, their silhouettes dwarfed by the towering gateway. On either side of the path, sheer cliffs drop into endless fog, with distant spires and hints of other ruins dissolving into the horizon. Small golden lanterns flicker on crumbling ledges, offering the only warmth in an otherwise foreboding and surreal landscape.
